# Microbiome App — Backend Project Brief

## Overview

This document outlines the full backend scope, database schema, scoring algorithm logic, API endpoints, and data import instructions for the Microbiome App backend (Supabase + API layer).

---

## Database Schema

### `products` Table

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid | Primary key |
| barcode | text | Unique barcode |
| product_name | text | Product name |
| brand | text | Brand name |
| category | text | Product category |
| size_count | text | Size/count descriptor (if available) |
| absorbency | text | Absorbency descriptor (if available) |
| ingredients_list | text | Raw/comma-separated ingredient list |
| material_composition | text | Product material details |
| bleaching_method | text | e.g. chlorine, unknown, N/A |
| synthetic_materials | text | Synthetic material details |
| preservatives | text | Preservative details |
| fragrance_type | text | scented / unscented / fragrance-free / etc. |
| antibacterial_agents | text | Antibacterial ingredient details |
| ph_level | text | Product pH range/value if known |
| usda_organic | boolean | true / false / null |
| gots_certified | boolean | true / false / null |
| oeko_tex_certified | boolean | true / false / null |
| gyno_approved | boolean | true / false / null |
| image_url | text | Product image URL |
| score | integer | Calculated normalized score (0–100) |
| source_url | text | |
| verified | boolean | true / false |

> **Compatibility note:** Legacy fields such as `name`, `organic`, and `certifications` may still exist in some environments for backward compatibility, but new writes should use the columns above.

